{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775894730319,"sessionID":"ses_2846fc3c8ffeySF8FCNZ5nIIcq","part":{"id":"prt_d7b90686d001FvX7QqiLfX7zaS","messageID":"msg_d7b903d0d0012jsviDAIZLjKpU","sessionID":"ses_2846fc3c8ffeySF8FCNZ5nIIcq","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_aa7af7934f75422f80e50ca4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"prompt":"Explore the current project structure to understand how OpenSpec changes are organized. Look for:\n1. Any existing `changes/` directory and its structure\n2. Any OpenSpec configuration files (like openspec.yaml, spec.md, etc.)\n3. Example change directories to understand the scaffold pattern\n4. The root project structure\n\nSearch thoroughly in the workspace root at /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z\n\nReturn:\n- The full directory tree of any existing changes/ directory\n- Contents of any OpenSpec config files\n- The structure of at least one example change directory if it exists\n- The overall project root structure","description":"Explore OpenSpec structure","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_2846f8435ffesmx7GZbUHIRVWh (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nNow I have a comprehensive picture. Here is my complete report:\n\n---\n\n## OpenSpec Change Organization -- Full Report\n\n### 1. Project Root Structure\n\n```\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/\n├── .github/                    # GitHub workflows and CI config\n├── .pytest_cache/              # Python test cache\n├── .sdd_prompt.md              # Prompt file\n├── agentd/                     # Idle cleanup controller (Go)\n├── bin/\n├── changes/                    # <<< OpenSpec change directories (40 entries: AR-001 to AR-040)\n├── ci-cd/                      # CI/CD spec\n├── cli-toolkit/                # CLI toolkit spec\n├── client-go/                  # Generated Kubernetes Go client\n├── cmd/                        # CLI and binaries\n├── code-execution/             # Code execution spec\n├── coverage.out\n├── delta-spec.md               # Root-level delta spec (for AR-038)\n├── deployment/                 # Deployment spec\n├── design.md                   # Root-level design doc (AR-040)\n├── docker/\n├── example/                    # Example applications (pcap-analyzer)\n├── go.mod / go.sum             # Go module files\n├── hack/\n├── idle-cleanup/               # Idle cleanup spec\n├── integrations/               # Integration specs (Dify plugin)\n├── Makefile\n├── manifests/                  # Helm charts, CRDs\n├── pkg/                        # Go source packages\n├── project.md                  # OpenSpec Project Context (AgentCube overview)\n├── proposal.md                 # Root-level proposal (AR-036)\n├── python-sdk/                 # Python SDK (agentcube-sdk)\n├── sandbox-orchestration/      # Sandbox orchestration spec\n├── session-routing/            # Session routing spec\n├── session-store/              # Session store spec\n├── tasks.md                    # Root-level tasks (AR-023)\n├── test_spec.md\n├── test/\n└── testing/\n```\n\n### 2. No OpenSpec Configuration Files Found\n\nThere are **no** `openspec.yaml`, `openspec.yml`, or similar OpenSpec configuration files in the project. The project does not use a formal OpenSpec tooling configuration file. Instead, conventions are established purely through file naming and directory structure.\n\n### 3. `changes/` Directory -- Full Tree\n\nThe `changes/` directory contains **40 change directories** (AR-001 through AR-040), each representing a single Atomic Requirement (AR) change:\n\n```\nchanges/\n├── AR-001/   (proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md)\n├── AR-002/   (proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md, delta-spec.md)\n├── AR-003/   (proposal.md, delta-spec.md)\n├── AR-004/   (proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md, delta-spec.md)\n├── AR-005/   (proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md, delta-spec.md)\n├── AR-006/   (proposal.md, delta-spec.md)\n├── AR-007/   (proposal.md, delta-spec.md)\n├── AR-008/   (proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md)\n├── AR-009/   (proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md)\n├── AR-010/   (proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md, delta-spec.md)\n├── AR-011/   (proposal.md, delta-spec.md)\n├── AR-012/   (proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md)\n├── AR-013/   (proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md)\n├── AR-014/   (proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md)\n├── AR-015/   (proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md)\n├── AR-016/   (proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md)\n├── AR-017/   (proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md, delta-spec.md)\n├── AR-018/   (proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md, delta-spec.md)\n├── AR-019/   (proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md, delta-spec.md)\n├── AR-020/   (proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md, delta-spec.md)\n├── AR-021/   (proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md, delta-spec.md)\n├── AR-022/   (proposal.md, delta-spec.md)\n├── AR-023/   (proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md, delta-spec.md)\n├── AR-024/   (proposal.md, delta-spec.md)\n├── AR-025/   (proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md, delta-spec.md)\n├── AR-026/   (proposal.md, delta-spec.md)\n├── AR-027/   (proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md, delta-spec.md)\n├── AR-028/   (proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md, delta-spec.md)\n├── AR-029/   (proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md, delta-spec.md)\n├── AR-030/   (proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md, delta-spec.md)\n├── AR-031/   (proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md, delta-spec.md)\n├── AR-032/   (proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md, delta-spec.md)\n├── AR-033/   (proposal.md, delta-spec.md)\n├── AR-034/   (proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md, delta-spec.md)\n├── AR-035/   (proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md, delta-spec.md)\n├── AR-036/   (proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md, delta-spec.md)\n├── AR-037/   (proposal.md, delta-spec.md)\n├── AR-038/   (proposal.md, delta-spec.md)\n├── AR-039/   (proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md, delta-spec.md)\n└── AR-040/   (proposal.md, design.md, tasks.md, delta-spec.md)\n```\n\n### 4. Scaffold Pattern for Change Directories\n\nEach change directory follows a consistent naming convention: `AR-NNN` (where NNN is a zero-padded 3-digit number). Each directory can contain up to **4 files**:\n\n| File | Required? | Purpose |\n|------|-----------|---------|\n| `proposal.md` | Always present | The change proposal: purpose, scope (in/out), impact analysis, alternatives considered, acceptance criteria, status checkboxes |\n| `design.md` | Most changes | Technical design: architecture, data structures, API contracts, error handling, testing strategy, implementation steps |\n| `tasks.md` | Most changes | Task breakdown: numbered tasks (T-1, T-2, ...) with checkbox sub-items, dependency graphs, parallelizable groups |\n| `delta-spec.md` | Many (not all) | Delta specification: Gherkin-style Given/When/Then scenarios for requirements (R-1, R-2, ...), file structure tables, dependency lists |\n\n**Variations observed:**\n- **Minimal** (AR-003, AR-006, AR-007, AR-011, AR-022, AR-024, AR-026, AR-033, AR-037, AR-038): `proposal.md` + `delta-spec.md` only -- no design.md or tasks.md\n- **Standard 3-file** (AR-001, AR-008, AR-009, AR-012, AR-013): `proposal.md` + `design.md` + `tasks.md` -- no delta-spec.md\n- **Full 4-file** (AR-002, AR-004, AR-005, AR-010, AR-017-AR-021, AR-023, AR-025, AR-027-AR-032, AR-034-AR-036, AR-039, AR-040): All four files present\n\n### 5. Example Change Directory Structures\n\n#### Example 1: AR-001 (3-file, early change)\n```\nchanges/AR-001/\n├── proposal.md    # CRD AgentRuntime type definition -- overview, metadata, purpose, scope, impact, alternatives, acceptance criteria, status\n├── design.md      # Architecture, package structure, data structures (Go types with code), API contracts (GVK/GVR/REST), error handling, test strategy, implementation steps\n└── tasks.md       # 14 tasks (T-001 through T-014) with numbered sub-items, acceptance criteria per task\n```\n\n#### Example 2: AR-040 (4-file, latest change)\n```\nchanges/AR-040/\n├── proposal.md    # Python SDK/CLI testing -- purpose, in/out scope, architecture summary, impact analysis, alternatives, acceptance criteria\n├── design.md      # Architecture (stub/template with TODOs), test strategy by sub-module, testing patterns (parametrized/async templates), coverage targets\n├── tasks.md       # 8 tasks (T-1 through T-8) with detailed sub-items, dependency graph, parallelizable groups, coverage targets summary\n└── delta-spec.md  # 12 requirements (R-1 through R-12) with Gherkin Given/When/Then scenarios for workloadmanager unit tests (sandbox create, reconciler, lifecycle, GC, etc.)\n```\n\n### 6. Root-Level Spec Files (Outside `changes/`)\n\nSeveral domain-specific `spec.md` files exist outside the `changes/` directory:\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/project.md` | Project context: AgentCube overview, tech stack, architecture diagram, conventions |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/delta-spec.md` | Root-level delta spec (for AR-038: Go unit tests for workloadmanager) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/proposal.md` | Root-level proposal (for AR-036: Dify plugin integration) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md` | Root-level design (for AR-040: Python SDK/CLI tests) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/tasks.md` | Root-level tasks (for AR-023: CLI invoke/status commands) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/test_spec.md` | Test spec file |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cli-toolkit/spec.md` | CLI toolkit spec |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/code-execution/spec.md` | Code execution spec |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/deployment/spec.md` | Deployment spec |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/idle-cleanup/spec.md` | Idle cleanup spec |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/integrations/spec.md` | Integrations spec |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/python-sdk/spec.md` | Python SDK spec |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/sandbox-orchestration/spec.md` | Sandbox orchestration spec |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/session-routing/spec.md` | Session routing spec |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/session-store/spec.md` | Session store spec |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/ci-cd/spec.md` | CI/CD spec |\n\n### 7. Key Observations\n\n1. **No formal OpenSpec tooling config**: The project does not use `openspec.yaml` or any OpenSpec CLI tool. The structure is purely convention-based.\n\n2. **Naming convention**: Changes are named `AR-NNN` (Atomic Requirement), sequentially numbered from AR-001 to AR-040.\n\n3. **File roles are well-defined**:\n   - `proposal.md` = What and Why (scope, impact, alternatives, acceptance criteria)\n   - `design.md` = How (architecture, data structures, API contracts, error handling, test strategy)\n   - `tasks.md` = Implementation plan (numbered tasks with checkboxes, dependency graphs, parallelizable groups)\n   - `delta-spec.md` = Behavioral specification (Gherkin Given/When/Then scenarios organized by requirement R-N)\n\n4. **Root-level spec files** exist for domain areas (each subdirectory like `cli-toolkit/`, `python-sdk/`, etc. has its own `spec.md`), while the `changes/` directory holds the incremental change artifacts.\n\n5. **Some root-level files** (`delta-spec.md`, `proposal.md`, `design.md`, `tasks.md` at the project root) appear to be working copies or the most recent change's files placed at the root level for convenience.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_2846f8435ffesmx7GZbUHIRVWh","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore OpenSpec structure","time":{"start":1775894559688,"end":1775894730316}}}}
