{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775894737096,"sessionID":"ses_2846fc3c8ffeySF8FCNZ5nIIcq","part":{"id":"prt_d7b932d09001ksLNzc6RAr4MON","messageID":"msg_d7b931699001KyKEWZC0zPgQtu","sessionID":"ses_2846fc3c8ffeySF8FCNZ5nIIcq","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_1e4cc8aa125848d888c900d3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-040/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-040/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-040 — Python SDK/CLI 测试\n2: \n3: **Module:** sdk-python/tests\n4: **Language:** Python\n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: 为 AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`) 建立完整的单元测试体系，覆盖所有公开 API 和内部组件，确保 SDK 的行为符合 spec 定义。测试体系包括控制平面客户端、数据平面客户端、高级客户端封装、异常层次结构、工具函数以及包导入/导出的验证，为后续迭代提供回归保护。\n10: \n11: ## Scope\n12: \n13: ### In Scope\n14: \n15: 1. **ControlPlaneClient 测试** (`test_control_plane.py`)\n16:    - 构造函数与 URL 解析（参数传入 / 环境变量 `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` / 缺失报错）\n17:    - 认证 Token 解析（参数传入 / K8s SA token 文件读取 / 文件不存在或空 token 处理）\n18:    - 默认与自定义超时参数、连接池配置\n19:    - `create_session` — 成功返回 sessionId、默认参数、缺少 sessionId 抛 ValueError、HTTP 错误传播、超时元组验证\n20:    - `delete_session` — 成功删除、404 视为成功、其他错误/连接异常/超时返回 False\n21:    - `close` — 释放 session、幂等性\n22:    - Session 复用 — 同一 session 用于多次请求\n23: \n24: 2. **CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient 测试** (`test_data_plane.py`)\n25:    - 构造函数与 base URL 构造（router_url+namespace+cr_name / 显式 base_url 覆盖 / 显式 base_url 忽略 router 参数）\n26:    - Session header `x-agentcube-session-id` 设置\n27:    - 默认与自定义超时、连接池配置、跨客户端 session 独立性\n28:    - `_request` — JSON body 设置 Content-Type、无 body 不覆盖、URL 构造、查询参数、HTTP 错误传播\n29:    - `execute_command` — 显式/默认超时、字符串转列表、列表原样传递、非零 exit code 抛 `CommandExecutionError`、超时 buffer 逻辑（+2.0s）\n30:    - `run_code` — Python/py/python3 语言别名、不支持语言抛 ValueError、超时传递\n31:    - `write_file` — base64 编码、空内容\n32:    - `upload_file` — multipart 上传带 session header、URL 构造\n33:    - `download_file` — 流式下载、去除 leading slash、HTTP 错误传播\n34:    - `list_files` — 指定路径 / 默认路径\n35:    - `close` — 释放 session、幂等性\n36: \n37: 3. **CodeInterpreterClient 测试** (`test_code_interpreter.py`)\n38:    - 初始化 — 无 session_id 时创建 session、提供 session_id 时复用、router_url 缺失抛 ValueError、从环境变量读取 router_url、verbose 控制 logger 级别、control plane 客户端参数传递\n39:    - 数据平面初始化失败 — 删除已创建 session、session_id 置 None、重新抛出异常\n40:    - Context manager — `__enter__` 返回 self、`__exit__` 调用 stop、with 语句正常流程、异常流程仍清理资源\n41:    - `stop` — 关闭 data plane、删除 control plane session、关闭 control plane client、幂等性\n42:    - `execute_command` — 委托到 data plane、字符串转列表、自定义超时（+2.0 buffer）、非零 exit code 抛 `CommandExecutionError`\n43:    - `run_code` — Python 代码写入文件并执行、不支持语言抛 ValueError\n44:    - 文件操作 — `write_file`/`upload_file`/`download_file`/`list_files` 委托到 data plane\n45:    - 集成测试 — 完整生命周期（创建 session → 执行命令 → 清理）、预配置 session 跳过控制平面\n46: \n47: 4. **AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient 测试** (`test_agent_runtime.py`)\n48:    - Base URL 构造（含/不含 trailing slash）、Session header 常量、HTTP adapter 与连接池配置\n49:    - `bootstrap_session_id` — 成功返回 header 值、header 缺失抛 ValueError、HTTP 错误传播、调用 raise_for_status\n50:    - `invoke` — 正确 URL/session header/JSON body、默认超时、显式超时、返回原始 response、调用 raise_for_status\n51:    - `close` — 释放 session、幂等性\n52: \n53: 5. **AgentRuntimeClient 测试** (`test_agent_runtime.py`)\n54:    - 初始化 — 仅 agent_name 使用全部默认值、显式参数存储所有字段、从环境变量解析 router_url、缺失 router_url 抛 ValueError、data plane 客户端参数传递\n55:    - Session 引导与复用 — session_id 为 None 触发 bootstrap、提供 session_id 跳过 bootstrap、verbose 控制 logger 级别\n56:    - Context manager — `__enter__` 返回 self、`__exit__` 正常/异常流程调用 close、with 语句正常/异常流程\n57:    - `invoke` — 有效 session 调用 data plane 并返回解析 JSON、session_id 为 None/空字符串抛 ValueError、自定义超时传递\n58:    - `close` — 委托到 data plane close、幂等性\n59:    - 集成测试 — 完整生命周期、预配置 session 跳过 bootstrap、自定义超时、异常流程仍清理、缺失 router_url 报错、bootstrap 缺失 header 报错\n60: \n61: 6. **异常层次结构测试** (`test_exceptions.py`)\n62:    - `AgentCubeError` — 是 Exception 子类、可抛出捕获\n63:    - `CommandExecutionError` — exit_code/stderr/command 属性、默认 command=None、消息格式、AgentCubeError 子类、可作为 AgentCubeError 捕获\n64:    - `SessionError` — AgentCubeError 子类、正确 docstring\n65:    - `DataPlaneError` — AgentCubeError 子类、正确 docstring\n66: \n67: 7. **包导入与公开导出测试** (`test_imports.py`)\n68:    - 所有客户端类可导入\n69:    - `agentcube.__all__` 仅包含 `CodeInterpreterClient` 和 `AgentRuntimeClient`\n70:    - `agentcube.clients.__all__` 包含三个 data/control plane 客户端\n71: \n72: 8. **工具函数测试** (`test_utils.py`)\n73:    - `create_session` — 返回 requests.Session、挂载 HTTPAdapter、自定义/默认连接池配置、可关闭\n74:    - `read_token_from_file` — 返回文件内容、去除空白、文件不存在返回空字符串\n75:    - `get_logger` — 返回 Logger 实例、默认 INFO 级别、DEBUG 级别、字符串/整数级别设置\n76: \n77: ### Out of Scope\n78: \n79: - E2E 集成测试（需要真实 Workload Manager 和 Router 服务）\n80: - CLI 工具测试（由其他 AR 覆盖）\n81: - 异步 I/O 版本 SDK 测试（当前 SDK 为同步实现）\n82: - 性能/压力测试\n83: - 修改任何生产代码（仅新增测试文件）\n84: \n85: ## Architecture Summary\n86: \n87: ### Current State\n88: \n89: - `python-sdk/agentcube/` 包含完整的 SDK 实现（control plane、data plane、高级客户端、异常、工具函数）\n90: - `python-sdk/tests/` 已有测试文件但为 TODO 骨架，无实际测试代码\n91: - 无 `conftest.py` 或 pytest fixtures\n92: - 无覆盖率报告机制\n93: \n94: ### Target State\n95: \n96: ```\n97: python-sdk/tests/\n98: ├── conftest.py              # pytest fixtures（mock_requests_session, mock_create_session）\n99: ├── test_control_plane.py    # ControlPlaneClient 测试（~370 行）\n100: ├── test_data_plane.py       # CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient 测试（~640 行）\n101: ├── test_code_interpreter.py # CodeInterpreterClient 测试（~635 行）\n102: ├── test_agent_runtime.py    # AgentRuntime* 测试（~840 行）\n103: ├── test_exceptions.py       # 异常层次结构测试（~80 行）\n104: ├── test_imports.py          # 包导入/导出测试（~55 行）\n105: └── test_utils.py            # 工具函数测试（~95 行）\n106: ```\n107: \n108: **测试策略**：\n109: - 使用 `pytest` 作为测试框架\n110: - `unittest.mock` / `pytest-mock` 模拟外部 HTTP 调用\n111: - 按组件分文件组织，每个文件内按功能分测试类\n112: - 所有 HTTP 交互通过 mock 避免网络依赖\n113: - 集成测试通过 mock 模拟完整生命周期\n114: \n115: ## Impact Analysis\n116: \n117: ### Dependencies\n118: \n119: | 依赖 | 来源 | 说明 |\n120: |------|------|------|\n121: | `pytest` | 开发依赖 | 测试框架 |\n122: | `pytest-mock` | 开发依赖 | pytest 的 mock 插件 |\n123: | `requests` | 运行时依赖 | SDK HTTP 客户端，测试中需 mock |\n124: | `agentcube-sdk` | 本地 | 被测模块 |\n125: \n126: ### Affected Components\n127: \n128: | 文件/目录 | 状态 | 说明 |\n129: |-----------|------|------|\n130: | `python-sdk/tests/conftest.py` | 新增 | pytest fixtures |\n131: | `python-sdk/tests/test_control_plane.py` | 新增 | ControlPlaneClient 测试 |\n132: | `python-sdk/tests/test_data_plane.py` | 新增 | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient 测试 |\n133: | `python-sdk/tests/test_code_interpreter.py` | 新增 | CodeInterpreterClient 测试 |\n134: | `python-sdk/tests/test_agent_runtime.py` | 新增 | AgentRuntime* 测试 |\n135: | `python-sdk/tests/test_exceptions.py` | 新增 | 异常层次结构测试 |\n136: | `python-sdk/tests/test_imports.py` | 新增 | 包导入/导出测试 |\n137: | `python-sdk/tests/test_utils.py` | 新增 | 工具函数测试 |\n138: | `python-sdk/agentcube/` | 无变更 | 仅作为被测模块 |\n139: \n140: ### Risk Assessment\n141: \n142: | 风险 | 等级 | 缓解措施 |\n143: |------|------|----------|\n144: | Mock 与真实 API 行为不一致 | 中 | 测试覆盖 spec 中定义的所有场景，包括边界条件 |\n145: | SDK API 变更导致测试失效 | 低 | 测试覆盖公开 API（`__all__` 导出），API 变更时同步更新测试 |\n146: | 测试执行速度慢 | 低 | 全部使用 mock，无网络调用，预期 < 5s |\n147: | 覆盖率不足遗漏 bug | 中 | 按 spec 逐条覆盖所有 Scenario，目标覆盖率 ≥ 80% |\n148: \n149: ## Alternatives Considered\n150: \n151: ### 1. pytest vs. unittest（✅ 选定 pytest）\n152: \n153: - **pytest**：fixture 机制、参数化测试、更简洁的断言语法、丰富的插件生态\n154: - **unittest**：Python 标准库自带、无需额外依赖、但 fixture 和参数化不如 pytest 灵活\n155: - **决策**：使用 pytest，与项目现有 `.pytest_cache` 结构一致\n156: \n157: ### 2. 全 Mock vs. HTTP 录制（✅ 选定全 Mock）\n158: \n159: - **全 Mock**：使用 `unittest.mock` 模拟所有 HTTP 调用，测试快速、可靠、无外部依赖\n160: - **HTTP 录制**（如 vcrpy）：录制真实请求回放，更贴近真实但需要初始真实环境\n161: - **决策**：全 Mock，当前阶段无真实服务可用，且 Mock 足以验证业务逻辑\n162: \n163: ### 3. 按文件组织 vs. 按功能组织（✅ 选定按文件组织）\n164: \n165: - **按文件组织**：每个源文件对应一个测试文件（`code_interpreter.py` → `test_code_interpreter.py`），结构清晰\n166: - **按功能组织**：按功能域分组（如 lifecycle、http、files），跨文件分散\n167: - **决策**：按文件组织，与源码结构一一对应，便于维护\n168: \n169: ## Upstream Dependencies\n170: \n171: - `agentcube-sdk` 生产代码已稳定（control plane、data plane、高级客户端、异常、工具函数）\n172: - Python >= 3.10（pyproject.toml 要求）\n173: - `requests`、`PyJWT`、`cryptography` 依赖已安装\n174: \n175: ## Test Strategy\n176: \n177: ### 测试分层\n178: \n179: | 层级 | 范围 | 工具 |\n180: |------|------|------|\n181: | 单元测试 | 单个类/函数的行为 | `unittest.mock`, `pytest-mock` |\n182: | 组件测试 | 类之间的协作（如 CodeInterpreterClient + ControlPlaneClient） | Mock 下游依赖 |\n183: | 集成测试 | 完整生命周期（init → operation → cleanup） | Mock 所有外部服务 |\n184: \n185: ### 测试模式\n186: \n187: 1. **Arrange-Act-Assert**：所有测试遵循三段式结构\n188: 2. **Mock 外部依赖**：所有 HTTP 调用通过 mock，不依赖网络\n189: 3. **边界条件覆盖**：空值、None、异常路径、错误码\n190: 4. **Spec 场景映射**：每个 spec Scenario 对应至少一个测试用例\n191: \n192: ### 覆盖率目标\n193: \n194: | 子模块 | 目标覆盖率 | 当前覆盖率 |\n195: |--------|-----------|-----------|\n196: | `agentcube/clients/` | ≥ 85% | 待测量 |\n197: | `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | ≥ 85% | 待测量 |\n198: | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | ≥ 85% | 待测量 |\n199: | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | 100% | 待测量 |\n200: | `agentcube/utils/` | ≥ 85% | 待测量 |\n201: | **Overall** | **≥ 80%** | **待测量** |\n202: \n203: ## Acceptance Criteria\n204: \n205: - [ ] 所有测试通过：`pytest python-sdk/tests/ -v` 无失败\n206: - [ ] 覆盖率达标：`pytest python-sdk/tests/ --cov=agentcube` 总体覆盖率 ≥ 80%\n207: - [ ] 无 warnings：测试运行无 pytest warnings\n208: - [ ] Spec 覆盖：每个 spec Scenario 有对应测试用例\n209: - [ ] Mock 隔离：无测试发起真实 HTTP 请求\n210: - [ ] 幂等性：关键方法（stop、close）测试幂等性\n211: - [ ] 异常路径：所有错误场景有对应测试\n\n(End of file - total 211 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-040 — Python SDK/CLI 测试\n\n**Module:** sdk-python/tests\n**Language:** Python\n**Size:** M\n\n## Purpose\n\n为 AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`) 建立完整的单元测试体系，覆盖所有公开 API 和内部组件，确保 SDK 的行为符合 spec 定义。测试体系包括控制平面客户端、数据平面客户端、高级客户端封装、异常层次结构、工具函数以及包导入/导出的验证，为后续迭代提供回归保护。\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n1. **ControlPlaneClient 测试** (`test_control_plane.py`)\n   - 构造函数与 URL 解析（参数传入 / 环境变量 `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` / 缺失报错）\n   - 认证 Token 解析（参数传入 / K8s SA token 文件读取 / 文件不存在或空 token 处理）\n   - 默认与自定义超时参数、连接池配置\n   - `create_session` — 成功返回 sessionId、默认参数、缺少 sessionId 抛 ValueError、HTTP 错误传播、超时元组验证\n   - `delete_session` — 成功删除、404 视为成功、其他错误/连接异常/超时返回 False","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-040/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775894737084,"end":1775894737094}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775894738568,"sessionID":"ses_2846fc3c8ffeySF8FCNZ5nIIcq","part":{"id":"prt_d7b93312a0017ouax6xgr4GVgS","messageID":"msg_d7b931699001KyKEWZC0zPgQtu","sessionID":"ses_2846fc3c8ffeySF8FCNZ5nIIcq","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_4c0c1fc15d5a424d84bbcf0e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-040/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-040/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-040: Python SDK/CLI 测试 — Design\n2: \n3: ## 1. Architecture\n4: \n5: ### 1.1 Purpose\n6: \n7: <!-- TODO: Describe the purpose -->\n8: \n9: ### 1.2 System Context\n10: \n11: ```\n12: python-sdk/\n13: ├── agentcube/\n14: │   ├── *.py\n15: │   └── *_test.py         # TODO — new test files\n16: └── tests/\n17:     ├── *_test.py         # TODO — new test files\n18:     └── conftest.py       # TODO — pytest fixtures\n19: ```\n20: \n21: ### 1.3 Design Principles\n22: \n23: - **pytest fixtures**: Reusable test setup/teardown via `conftest.py`\n24: - **Parametrized tests**: `@pytest.mark.parametrize` for data-driven test cases\n25: - **No production code changes**: Only test file additions\n26: - **Mock external services**: Use `unittest.mock` / `pytest-mock` for API/HTTP calls\n27: - **Async test support**: `pytest-asyncio` for async SDK methods\n28: \n29: ---\n30: \n31: ## 2. Test Strategy by Sub-Module\n32: \n33: ### 2.1 agentcube/\n34: \n35: | Test Category | Approach |\n36: |---------------|----------|\n37: | TODO | TODO |\n38: \n39: ### 2.2 tests/\n40: \n41: | Test Category | Approach |\n42: |---------------|----------|\n43: | TODO | TODO |\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ## 3. Testing Patterns\n48: \n49: ### 3.1 Parametrized Test Template\n50: \n51: ```python\n52: import pytest\n53: \n54: @pytest.mark.parametrize(\"input_val,expected\", [\n55:     # TODO: add test cases\n56: ])\n57: def test_foo(input_val, expected):\n58:     # Arrange, Act, Assert\n59:     assert result == expected\n60: ```\n61: \n62: ### 3.2 Async Test Template\n63: \n64: ```python\n65: import pytest\n66: \n67: @pytest.mark.asyncio\n68: async def test_async_foo():\n69:     # Arrange, Act, Assert\n70:     assert await async_func() == expected\n71: ```\n72: \n73: ---\n74: \n75: ## 4. Coverage Targets\n76: \n77: | Sub-Module | Target Coverage | Rationale |\n78: |------------|-----------------|-----------|\n79: | agentcube/ | TODO | TODO |\n80: | tests/ | TODO | TODO |\n81: \n82: ---\n83: \n84: ## 5. Implementation Notes\n85: \n86: <!-- TODO: Add implementation-specific notes -->\n\n(End of file - total 86 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-040: Python SDK/CLI 测试 — Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\n<!-- TODO: Describe the purpose -->\n\n### 1.2 System Context\n\n```\npython-sdk/\n├── agentcube/\n│   ├── *.py\n│   └── *_test.py         # TODO — new test files\n└── tests/\n    ├── *_test.py         # TODO — new test files\n    └── conftest.py       # TODO — pytest fixtures\n```\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-040/design.md","time":{"start":1775894738559,"end":1775894738567}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775894739619,"sessionID":"ses_2846fc3c8ffeySF8FCNZ5nIIcq","part":{"id":"prt_d7b933727001mEnO43maBoPaOz","messageID":"msg_d7b931699001KyKEWZC0zPgQtu","sessionID":"ses_2846fc3c8ffeySF8FCNZ5nIIcq","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_60ec690973b84458986c1c1c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-040/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-040/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-040: Python SDK/CLI 测试 — Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** `sdk-python/tests` | **Language:** Python | **Size:** M\n4: **Base specs:** `python-sdk/agentcube/`, `python-sdk/tests/` source code\n5: **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## T-1: Fix existing test bugs and failing tests\n10: \n11: - [ ] Fix `test_code_interpreter.py` — rename 3 methods in `TestStop` class to add `test_` prefix: `stop_closes_dp_client` → `test_stop_closes_dp_client`, `stop_deletes_session` → `test_stop_deletes_session`, `stop_closes_cp_client` → `test_stop_closes_cp_client`\n12: - [ ] Fix `test_control_plane.py` — 5 failing tests in `TestCreateSession` and `TestSessionReuse` (mock `session.post` returns dict instead of Response object with `.json()` method)\n13: - [ ] Fix `test_data_plane.py` — `test_request_url_construction` failing (mock `session.request` kwargs mismatch: `url` key missing)\n14: - [ ] Run `pytest python-sdk/tests/ -v` — verify all existing tests pass (172 tests, 0 failures)\n15: \n16: ---\n17: \n18: ## T-2: Extend `test_code_interpreter.py` — CodeInterpreterClient gaps\n19: \n20: - [ ] `test_stop_when_session_id_is_none` — session_id=None → skips delete_session, still closes dp and cp clients\n21: - [ ] `test_stop_when_dp_client_not_initialized` — no dp_client attribute → no crash (hasattr guard)\n22: - [ ] `test_stop_when_cp_client_not_initialized` — no cp_client attribute → no crash (hasattr guard)\n23: - [ ] `test_stop_idempotent` — multiple stop() calls → each cleanup action called exactly once\n24: - [ ] `test_run_code_python3_language` — `\"python3\"` → writes .py file + executes via python3\n25: - [ ] `test_run_code_py_language` — `\"py\"` → writes .py file + executes via python3\n26: - [ ] `test_run_code_case_insensitive` — `\"PYTHON\"` → writes .py file + executes via python3\n27: - [ ] `test_run_code_passes_timeout_to_execute` — `timeout=30.0` → passed through to execute_command\n28: - [ ] `test_run_code_unsupported_language` — `\"ruby\"` → raises `ValueError(\"Unsupported language: ruby\")`\n29: - [ ] `test_execute_command_with_list_input` — `[\"ls\", \"-la\"]` → passed as-is to dp (not double-wrapped)\n30: - [ ] `test_execute_command_empty_string` — `\"\"` → `[\"\"]` sent to dp\n31: - [ ] `test_session_created_flag_true_when_no_session_id` — `_session_created=True` when session_id=None\n32: - [ ] `test_session_created_flag_false_when_session_id_provided` — `_session_created=False` when session_id provided\n33: - [ ] `test_data_plane_init_failure_deletes_session` — DP init raises → delete_session called, session_id=None, exception re-raised\n34: - [ ] `test_data_plane_init_failure_no_cleanup_for_reused_session` — `_session_created=False` + DP init fails → no delete_session, exception re-raised\n35: - [ ] `test_data_plane_init_called_with_correct_params` — session_id, router_url, namespace, cr_name passed to DP constructor\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ## T-3: Extend `test_data_plane.py` — CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient gaps\n40: \n41: - [ ] `test_execute_command_http_error_propagates` — HTTP 500 → raise_for_status propagates HTTPError\n42: - [ ] `test_execute_command_timeout_buffer_explicit` — `timeout=30` → request timeout tuple `(connect_timeout, 32.0)`\n43: - [ ] `test_execute_command_timeout_buffer_default` — `timeout=None`, default 120 → request timeout `(connect_timeout, 122.0)`\n44: - [ ] `test_execute_command_timeout_string_in_body` — body `timeout` field is `\"30s\"` (original value, not buffered)\n45: - [ ] `test_write_file_http_error_propagates` — HTTP error → raise_for_status propagates\n46: - [ ] `test_write_file_unicode_content` — Unicode string → base64 encoded correctly in JSON body\n47: - [ ] `test_write_file_empty_content` — empty string → base64 of `\"\"` sent\n48: - [ ] `test_upload_file_session_header_present` — POST headers include `x-agentcube-session-id`\n49: - [ ] `test_upload_file_no_json_content_type` — request does NOT set `Content-Type: application/json` (multipart)\n50: - [ ] `test_upload_file_nonexistent_raises_io_error` — file not found → FileNotFoundError propagates\n51: - [ ] `test_upload_file_http_error_propagates` — HTTP error → raise_for_status propagates\n52: - [ ] `test_download_file_strips_leading_slash` — `/remote/path` → endpoint `api/files/remote/path`\n53: - [ ] `test_download_file_relative_path_unchanged` — `relative/path` → endpoint `api/files/relative/path`\n54: - [ ] `test_download_file_creates_local_file` — verifies file content written to local path correctly\n55: - [ ] `test_download_file_http_error_propagates` — HTTP error → raise_for_status propagates\n56: - [ ] `test_list_files_http_error_propagates` — HTTP error → raise_for_status propagates\n57: - [ ] `test_list_files_default_path` — no path arg → `path=\".\"` in query params\n58: - [ ] `test_run_code_delegates_to_write_and_execute` — full delegation path: write_file + execute_command called\n59: - [ ] `test_run_code_python_file_extension` — remote path ends with `.py`\n60: - [ ] `test_request_default_timeout_tuple` — no timeout override → `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)`\n61: - [ ] `test_request_custom_timeout_override` — timeout kwarg → used instead of default\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: ## T-4: Extend `test_control_plane.py` — ControlPlaneClient gaps\n66: \n67: - [ ] `test_create_session_with_none_metadata` — `metadata=None` → body includes `\"metadata\": null`\n68: - [ ] `test_create_session_url_with_trailing_slash` — base_url with trailing slash → URL constructed correctly (no double slash)\n69: - [ ] `test_create_session_default_params` — no args → body `{\"name\": \"my-interpreter\", \"namespace\": \"default\", \"ttl\": 3600, \"metadata\": null}`\n70: - [ ] `test_delete_session_url_construction` — verifies exact URL format `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{id}`\n71: - [ ] `test_delete_session_404_returns_true` — HTTP 404 → returns True (idempotent)\n72: - [ ] `test_delete_session_500_returns_false` — HTTP 500 → logs warning, returns False\n73: - [ ] `test_delete_session_request_exception_returns_false` — RequestException → logs warning, returns False\n74: - [ ] `test_session_headers_content_type_always_set` — `Content-Type: application/json` always in session headers\n75: - [ ] `test_auth_token_explicit_takes_priority` — explicit auth_token → SA file not read, Bearer token set\n76: - [ ] `test_auth_token_from_sa_file` — no auth_token → reads SA file, sets Bearer token\n77: - [ ] `test_auth_token_sa_file_missing` — no auth_token, SA file missing → no Authorization header\n78: - [ ] `test_auth_token_empty_string_no_header` — `auth_token=\"\"` → no Authorization header set\n79: - [ ] `test_workload_manager_url_from_env` — no arg, WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL set → uses env var\n80: - [ ] `test_workload_manager_url_missing_raises` — no arg, no env → raises ValueError\n81: \n82: ---\n83: \n84: ## T-5: Extend `test_agent_runtime.py` — AgentRuntime* gaps\n85: \n86: - [ ] `test_dp_invoke_http_error_propagates` — HTTP error → raise_for_status propagates\n87: - [ ] `test_dp_invoke_with_empty_payload` — `{}` → valid POST request\n88: - [ ] `test_dp_invoke_per_request_session_header` — `invoke(session_id=\"s1\")` → header `x-agentcube-session-id: s1`\n89: - [ ] `test_dp_invoke_timeout_tuple_default` — `timeout=None` → `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)`\n90: - [ ] `test_dp_invoke_timeout_tuple_custom` — `timeout=60` → `(connect_timeout, 60)`\n91: - [ ] `test_dp_bootstrap_session_id_empty_string_raises` — header value `\"\"` → raises ValueError\n92: - [ ] `test_dp_close_delegates_to_session_close` — verifies session.close() called\n93: - [ ] `test_dp_close_idempotent` — multiple close() calls → session.close() called each time\n94: - [ ] `test_ar_client_invoke_returns_parsed_json` — data plane returns response → invoke() returns `resp.json()` dict\n95: - [ ] `test_ar_client_invoke_session_id_none_raises` — session_id=None → invoke raises ValueError\n96: - [ ] `test_ar_client_invoke_session_id_empty_raises` — session_id=\"\" → invoke raises ValueError\n97: - [ ] `test_ar_client_invoke_custom_timeout` — `timeout=60` → passed to dp_client.invoke\n98: - [ ] `test_ar_client_close_delegates_to_dp_close` — verifies dp_client.close() called\n99: - [ ] `test_ar_client_close_idempotent` — multiple close() calls → dp_client.close() called each time\n100: - [ ] `test_ar_client_bootstrap_triggers_when_no_session_id` — session_id=None → bootstrap_session_id called\n101: - [ ] `test_ar_client_bootstrap_skipped_when_session_id_provided` — session_id provided → bootstrap_session_id NOT called\n102: - [ ] `test_ar_client_context_manager_exit_with_exception` — exception in with block → close() still called, exception propagates\n103: \n104: ---\n105: \n106: ## T-6: Extend `test_utils.py` — Utility function gaps\n107: \n108: - [ ] `test_read_token_from_file_empty_file` — empty file → returns `\"\"`\n109: - [ ] `test_read_token_from_file_multiline_strips` — `\"token\\n\\n\"` → returns `\"token\"`\n110: - [ ] `test_read_token_from_file_whitespace_only` — `\"  \\n  \\n\"` → returns `\"\"`\n111: - [ ] `test_get_logger_handler_not_duplicated` — second call with same name → only 1 handler on logger\n112: - [ ] `test_get_logger_formatter_is_set` — handler has Formatter with correct format string\n113: - [ ] `test_get_logger_handler_is_stream_handler` — handler type is StreamHandler\n114: - [ ] `test_get_logger_string_level` — `level=\"DEBUG\"` → logger level = 10\n115: - [ ] `test_create_session_independent_instances` — two calls → two independent Session objects (different ids)\n116: - [ ] `test_create_session_default_pool_config` — default pool_connections=10, pool_maxsize=10\n117: \n118: ---\n119: \n120: ## T-7: Create `test_integration.py` — Cross-component integration tests\n121: \n122: - [ ] `test_ci_full_lifecycle_create_execute_stop` — CodeInterpreterClient: create session → execute_command → stop (all mocks verified)\n123: - [ ] `test_ci_context_manager_with_exception` — exception in `with` block → stop() still called, exception propagates\n124: - [ ] `test_ci_context_manager_normal_exit` — no exception → stop() called on normal exit\n125: - [ ] `test_ci_pre_provisioned_session_no_control_plane_calls` — session_id provided → no create_session/delete_session called\n126: - [ ] `test_ci_data_plane_init_failure_cleanup` — DP init raises → delete_session called, session_id=None, exception re-raised\n127: - [ ] `test_ci_session_created_flag_true_triggers_cleanup` — `_session_created=True` + DP failure → cleanup happens\n128: - [ ] `test_ci_session_created_flag_false_skips_cleanup` — `_session_created=False` + DP failure → no cleanup\n129: - [ ] `test_ar_full_lifecycle_bootstrap_invoke_close` — AgentRuntimeClient: bootstrap → invoke → close (all mocks verified)\n130: - [ ] `test_ar_context_manager_with_exception` — exception in `with` block → close() still called, exception propagates\n131: - [ ] `test_ar_pre_provisioned_session_no_bootstrap` — session_id provided → bootstrap_session_id NOT called\n132: - [ ] `test_ar_missing_session_id_invoke_raises` — bootstrap returns None → invoke raises ValueError\n133: - [ ] `test_ci_execute_command_timeout_propagation` — custom timeout → +2.0 buffer → DP receives correct timeout tuple\n134: - [ ] `test_ar_invoke_timeout_propagation` — custom timeout → DP receives correct timeout tuple\n135: - [ ] `test_ci_run_code_python_writes_and_executes` — run_code(\"python\", \"print(1)\") → write_file + execute_command called with correct args\n136: - [ ] `test_ci_run_code_unsupported_language` — run_code(\"ruby\", \"...\") → ValueError raised\n137: - [ ] `test_ci_file_operations_delegation` — write/upload/download/list all delegate to DP client with correct args\n138: - [ ] `test_cp_create_and_delete_session_flow` — ControlPlaneClient: create_session → delete_session → verify URLs and HTTP methods\n139: - [ ] `test_dp_execute_command_exit_code_error` — CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient: non-zero exit → CommandExecutionError raised\n140: - [ ] `test_env_var_precedence_router_url` — CodeInterpreterClient: arg takes precedence over ROUTER_URL env var\n141: - [ ] `test_env_var_precedence_workload_manager_url` — ControlPlaneClient: arg takes precedence over WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL env var\n142: \n143: ---\n144: \n145: ## T-8: Run full test suite and verify coverage\n146: \n147: - [ ] `pytest python-sdk/tests/ -v` — all tests pass (expected ~230+ tests, 0 failures)\n148: - [ ] `pytest python-sdk/tests/ --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing` — generate coverage report\n149: - [ ] Verify overall coverage ≥ 80% (target >92%)\n150: - [ ] Verify `agentcube/exceptions.py` coverage = 100%\n151: - [ ] Verify `agentcube/utils/http.py` coverage = 100%\n152: - [ ] Verify `agentcube/utils/utils.py` coverage = 100%\n153: - [ ] Verify `agentcube/utils/log.py` coverage > 90%\n154: - [ ] Verify `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` coverage > 95%\n155: - [ ] Verify `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` coverage > 95%\n156: - [ ] Verify `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` coverage > 95%\n157: - [ ] Verify `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` coverage > 95%\n158: - [ ] Verify `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` coverage > 95%\n159: - [ ] `pytest python-sdk/tests/ --cov=agentcube` — no pytest warnings\n160: - [ ] Verify no test makes real HTTP requests (all mocked)\n161: - [ ] Run `ruff check python-sdk/tests/` — no lint violations\n162: \n163: ---\n164: \n165: ## Dependency Graph\n166: \n167: ```\n168: T-1 ──┬── T-2 ──┐\n169:       ├── T-3 ──┤\n170:       ├── T-4 ──┼── T-7 ── T-8\n171:       ├── T-5 ──┤\n172:       └── T-6 ──┘\n173: ```\n174: \n175: ## Parallelizable Groups\n176: \n177: | Group | Tasks | Prerequisites | Notes |\n178: |-------|-------|---------------|-------|\n179: | G1 | T-1 | None | Must complete first — fixes broken tests |\n180: | G2 | T-2, T-3, T-4, T-5, T-6 | T-1 | All extend existing test files independently |\n181: | G3 | T-7 | T-2, T-3, T-4, T-5 | Integration tests depend on understanding all components |\n182: | G4 | T-8 | T-2, T-3, T-4, T-5, T-6, T-7 | Final verification gate |\n183: \n184: ## Coverage Targets Summary\n185: \n186: | Subpackage | Target | Current | Gap |\n187: |------------|--------|---------|-----|\n188: | `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | >95% | 99% (1 line missing) | Fix 3 skipped stop tests + 16 new tests |\n189: | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | >95% | 100% | Add 13 edge case tests |\n190: | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | >95% | 98% (1 line missing) | Add 14 SA token + error handling tests |\n191: | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | >95% | 100% | Add 21 timeout/multipart/download tests |\n192: | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | >95% | 100% | Add 9 header/timeout/close tests |\n193: | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | 100% | 100% | Already covered |\n194: | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | 100% | 100% | Add 1 independent instances test |\n195: | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | 100% | 100% | Add 3 edge case tests |\n196: | `agentcube/utils/log.py` | >90% | 100% | Add 3 handler/formatter tests |\n197: | **Overall** | **>92%** | **99%** | **~60 new tests across 6 files** |\n\n(End of file - total 197 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-040: Python SDK/CLI 测试 — Tasks\n\n**Module:** `sdk-python/tests` | **Language:** Python | **Size:** M\n**Base specs:** `python-sdk/agentcube/`, `python-sdk/tests/` source code\n**Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n\n---\n\n## T-1: Fix existing test bugs and failing tests\n\n- [ ] Fix `test_code_interpreter.py` — rename 3 methods in `TestStop` class to add `test_` prefix: `stop_closes_dp_client` → `test_stop_closes_dp_client`, `stop_deletes_session` → `test_stop_deletes_session`, `stop_closes_cp_client` → `test_stop_closes_cp_client`\n- [ ] Fix `test_control_plane.py` — 5 failing tests in `TestCreateSession` and `TestSessionReuse` (mock `session.post` returns dict instead of Response object with `.json()` method)\n- [ ] Fix `test_data_plane.py` — `test_request_url_construction` failing (mock `session.request` kwargs mismatch: `url` key missing)\n- [ ] Run `pytest python-sdk/tests/ -v` — verify all existing tests pass (172 tests, 0 failures)\n\n---\n\n## T-2: Extend `test_code_interpreter.py` — CodeInterpreterClient gaps\n\n- [ ] `test_stop_when_session_id_is_none` — session_id=None → skips delete_session, still closes dp and cp clients","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-040/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775894739612,"end":1775894739617}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775894741007,"sessionID":"ses_2846fc3c8ffeySF8FCNZ5nIIcq","part":{"id":"prt_d7b933b04001AwsYk1cID47tW5","messageID":"msg_d7b931699001KyKEWZC0zPgQtu","sessionID":"ses_2846fc3c8ffeySF8FCNZ5nIIcq","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_071d0f0f0e1d4daca880d1d6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-040/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-040/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-040: Python SDK/CLI 测试 — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `sdk-python/tests`\n6: - **Language:** Python\n7: - **Size:** M\n8: - **Base specs:** `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n9: \n10: ## Scope\n11: \n12: This delta spec defines the test coverage requirements for the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`). Existing tests cover basic initialization, delegation, and happy paths for all client classes. This spec identifies **gaps** between the existing test suite and the specification, and defines acceptance scenarios for the missing coverage.\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## R-1: CodeInterpreterClient — data plane init failure recovery\n17: \n18: **Scope:** `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` — `__init__`, `_init_data_plane`\n19: \n20: ### Requirement: Data plane init failure cleans up session\n21: \n22: #### Scenario: Data plane init failure after session create\n23: \n24: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is initialized without a `session_id`\n25:   AND `ControlPlaneClient.create_session` returns a valid session ID\n26: - **WHEN** `_init_data_plane()` raises an exception\n27: - **THEN** the client SHALL log a warning\n28:   AND call `delete_session(session_id)` on the control plane client\n29:   AND set `self.session_id` to `None`\n30:   AND re-raise the original exception\n31: \n32: ---\n33: \n34: ## R-2: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient — execute_command timeout buffer\n35: \n36: **Scope:** `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` — `execute_command`\n37: \n38: ### Requirement: Timeout buffer (+2.0s) applied to read timeout\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Explicit timeout gets buffer\n41: \n42: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.execute_command(command, timeout=30)`\n43: - **WHEN** the HTTP request is constructed\n44: - **THEN** the request timeout tuple SHALL be `(connect_timeout, 32.0)` (i.e., `timeout + 2.0`)\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: Default timeout gets buffer\n47: \n48: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.execute_command(command, timeout=None)`\n49:   AND `self.timeout` defaults to `120`\n50: - **WHEN** the HTTP request is constructed\n51: - **THEN** the effective timeout SHALL be `120`\n52:   AND the request read timeout SHALL be `122.0` (i.e., `120 + 2.0`)\n53: \n54: #### Scenario: Timeout buffer in PicoD timeout string\n55: \n56: - **GIVEN** `execute_command(command, timeout=30)`\n57: - **WHEN** the JSON body is constructed\n58: - **THEN** the body `timeout` field SHALL be `\"30s\"` (original value, not buffered)\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ## R-3: ControlPlaneClient — SA token file fallback\n63: \n64: **Scope:** `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` — `__init__`\n65: \n66: ### Requirement: Auth token resolution from SA file\n67: \n68: #### Scenario: Auth token read from SA file\n69: \n70: - **GIVEN** `auth_token` is not provided to `ControlPlaneClient`\n71:   AND `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is set\n72: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n73: - **THEN** it SHALL call `read_token_from_file(\"/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token\")`\n74:   AND if the returned token is non-empty, set `Authorization: Bearer {token}` on the session\n75: \n76: #### Scenario: SA token file not found\n77: \n78: - **GIVEN** `auth_token` is not provided\n79:   AND the SA token file does not exist (`read_token_from_file` returns `\"\"`)\n80: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n81: - **THEN** no `Authorization` header SHALL be set on the session\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Explicit auth_token takes priority over SA file\n84: \n85: - **GIVEN** `auth_token=\"explicit-token\"` is provided\n86: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n87: - **THEN** `read_token_from_file` SHALL NOT be called\n88:   AND `Authorization: Bearer explicit-token` SHALL be set on the session\n89: \n90: ---\n91: \n92: ## R-4: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient — run_code Python execution flow\n93: \n94: **Scope:** `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` — `run_code`\n95: \n96: ### Requirement: Python code writes file then executes\n97: \n98: #### Scenario: run_code writes timestamped .py file then executes\n99: \n100: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.run_code(\"python\", \"print('hello')\")`\n101: - **WHEN** the method runs\n102: - **THEN** it SHALL call `write_file` with content containing the code\n103:   AND the remote path SHALL end with `.py`\n104:   AND it SHALL call `execute_command` with `python3 <remote_path>`\n105: \n106: #### Scenario: run_code language aliases (py, python3)\n107: \n108: - **GIVEN** `run_code` is called with `language` = `\"py\"` or `\"python3\"`\n109: - **WHEN** the method runs\n110: - **THEN** it SHALL follow the same write-file-then-execute path as `\"python\"`\n111: \n112: #### Scenario: run_code unsupported language\n113: \n114: - **GIVEN** `run_code` is called with an unsupported language (e.g., `\"javascript\"`)\n115: - **WHEN** the method runs\n116: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` with message containing `\"Unsupported language\"`\n117: \n118: ---\n119: \n120: ## R-5: CodeInterpreterClient — context manager exception handling\n121: \n122: **Scope:** `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` — `__enter__`, `__exit__`, `stop`\n123: \n124: ### Requirement: Context manager cleans up on exception\n125: \n126: #### Scenario: Context manager exit with exception\n127: \n128: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager\n129:   AND an exception is raised inside the `with` block\n130: - **WHEN** the block exits\n131: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`\n132:   AND the data plane client SHALL be closed\n133:   AND the control plane session SHALL be deleted (if `session_id` was set)\n134:   AND the original exception SHALL propagate\n135: \n136: #### Scenario: Context manager exit without exception\n137: \n138: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used as a context manager\n139:   AND no exception occurs in the block\n140: - **WHEN** the block exits normally\n141: - **THEN** `__exit__` SHALL call `stop()`\n142:   AND all resources SHALL be cleaned up\n143: \n144: ---\n145: \n146: ## R-6: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient — invoke header management\n147: \n148: **Scope:** `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` — `invoke`\n149: \n150: ### Requirement: Per-request header isolation\n151: \n152: #### Scenario: Invoke sets session header per request\n153: \n154: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient.invoke(session_id=\"test-session\", payload={...})`\n155: - **WHEN** the POST request is made\n156: - **THEN** the request SHALL include header `x-agentcube-session-id: test-session`\n157:   AND the request SHALL include header `Content-Type: application/json`\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: Invoke timeout tuple construction\n160: \n161: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` with `connect_timeout=5.0`, `timeout=120`\n162:   AND `invoke(..., timeout=None)` is called\n163: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n164: - **THEN** the timeout parameter SHALL be `(5.0, 120)`\n165: \n166: #### Scenario: Invoke with custom timeout\n167: \n168: - **GIVEN** `invoke(session_id=\"s\", payload={}, timeout=60)`\n169: - **WHEN** the request is sent\n170: - **THEN** the timeout parameter SHALL be `(5.0, 60)`\n171: \n172: ---\n173: \n174: ## R-7: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient — multipart upload headers\n175: \n176: **Scope:** `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` — `upload_file`\n177: \n178: ### Requirement: Multipart upload includes session header, not JSON Content-Type\n179: \n180: #### Scenario: Multipart upload includes session header\n181: \n182: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient.upload_file(local_path, remote_path)`\n183: - **WHEN** the POST request is made\n184: - **THEN** the request headers SHALL include `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n185:   AND the request SHALL use `files={'file': ...}` and `data={'path', 'mode'}` parameters\n186:   AND the request SHALL NOT set `Content-Type: application/json`\n187: \n188: ---\n189: \n190: ## R-8: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient — download file path cleaning\n191: \n192: **Scope:** `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` — `download_file`\n193: \n194: ### Requirement: Leading slash stripped from remote path\n195: \n196: #### Scenario: Download strips leading slash\n197: \n198: - **GIVEN** `download_file(\"/remote/path\", local_path)`\n199: - **WHEN** the GET request is constructed\n200: - **THEN** the endpoint SHALL be `api/files/remote/path` (without leading slash)\n201: \n202: #### Scenario: Download relative path unchanged\n203: \n204: - **GIVEN** `download_file(\"relative/path\", local_path)`\n205: - **WHEN** the GET request is constructed\n206: - **THEN** the endpoint SHALL be `api/files/relative/path`\n207: \n208: ---\n209: \n210: ## R-9: ControlPlaneClient — delete_session error handling\n211: \n212: **Scope:** `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` — `delete_session`\n213: \n214: ### Requirement: 404 treated as success, other errors logged\n215: \n216: #### Scenario: Delete session returns 404\n217: \n218: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"nonexistent-session\")`\n219: - **WHEN** the server returns HTTP 404\n220: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `True`\n221: \n222: #### Scenario: Delete session other HTTP error\n223: \n224: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session\")`\n225: - **WHEN** the server returns HTTP 500 or raises `HTTPError`\n226: - **THEN** the method SHALL log the error\n227:   AND return `False`\n228: \n229: #### Scenario: Delete session request exception\n230: \n231: - **GIVEN** `delete_session(\"session\")`\n232: - **WHEN** a `requests.exceptions.RequestException` is raised\n233: - **THEN** the method SHALL log the error\n234:   AND return `False`\n235: \n236: ---\n237: \n238: ## R-10: AgentRuntimeClient — invoke response parsing\n239: \n240: **Scope:** `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` — `invoke`\n241: \n242: ### Requirement: Invoke returns parsed JSON\n243: \n244: #### Scenario: Invoke returns parsed JSON dict\n245: \n246: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient.invoke({\"key\": \"value\"})`\n247:   AND the data plane returns a response with JSON body `{\"result\": \"success\"}`\n248: - **WHEN** the method completes\n249: - **THEN** it SHALL return `{\"result\": \"success\"}` (parsed dict, not raw response object)\n250: \n251: ---\n252: \n253: ## R-11: Package exports — public API surface\n254: \n255: **Scope:** `agentcube/__init__.py`, `agentcube/clients/__init__.py`\n256: \n257: ### Requirement: Root __all__ contains only public clients\n258: \n259: #### Scenario: Root __all__ exports\n260: \n261: - **GIVEN** `import agentcube`\n262: - **WHEN** `agentcube.__all__` is inspected\n263: - **THEN** it SHALL equal `[\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]`\n264: \n265: ### Requirement: Clients submodule exports internal clients\n266: \n267: #### Scenario: Clients __all__ exports\n268: \n269: - **GIVEN** `from agentcube import clients`\n270: - **WHEN** `clients.__all__` is inspected\n271: - **THEN** it SHALL contain `\"ControlPlaneClient\"`, `\"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\"`, `\"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\"`\n272: \n273: ---\n274: \n275: ## R-12: ControlPlaneClient — create_session URL and body\n276: \n277: **Scope:** `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` — `create_session`\n278: \n279: ### Requirement: Create session HTTP contract\n280: \n281: #### Scenario: POST to correct URL with correct body\n282: \n283: - **GIVEN** `ControlPlaneClient` with `base_url = \"http://wm\"`\n284: - **WHEN** `create_session(name=\"test\", namespace=\"ns\", ttl=7200, metadata={\"k\": \"v\"})` is called\n285: - **THEN** the request SHALL be `POST http://wm/v1/code-interpreter`\n286:   AND the JSON body SHALL be `{\"name\": \"test\", \"namespace\": \"ns\", \"ttl\": 7200, \"metadata\": {\"k\": \"v\"}}`\n287:   AND the response `data[\"sessionId\"]` SHALL be returned\n288: \n289: #### Scenario: Default parameters in create_session\n290: \n291: - **GIVEN** `create_session()` called with no arguments\n292: - **WHEN** the request is constructed\n293: - **THEN** the JSON body SHALL be `{\"name\": \"my-interpreter\", \"namespace\": \"default\", \"ttl\": 3600, \"metadata\": None}`\n294: \n295: ---\n296: \n297: ## R-13: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient — write_file base64 encoding\n298: \n299: **Scope:** `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` — `write_file`\n300: \n301: ### Requirement: File content base64 encoded\n302: \n303: #### Scenario: write_file encodes content as base64\n304: \n305: - **GIVEN** `write_file(\"hello world\", \"/path/to/file\")`\n306: - **WHEN** the POST request is constructed\n307: - **THEN** the JSON body `content` field SHALL be the base64 encoding of `\"hello world\"`\n308:   AND the body `path` SHALL be `\"/path/to/file\"`\n309:   AND the body `mode` SHALL be `\"0644\"`\n310: \n311: ---\n312: \n313: ## R-14: AgentRuntimeClient — bootstrap session ID failure\n314: \n315: **Scope:** `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` — `__init__`\n316: \n317: ### Requirement: Bootstrap failure raises ValueError\n318: \n319: #### Scenario: Missing session header on bootstrap\n320: \n321: - **GIVEN** `AgentRuntimeClient` is initialized without `session_id`\n322:   AND the GET request to the invocation base URL returns no `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n323: - **WHEN** the client initializes\n324: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` with message `\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n325: \n326: ---\n327: \n328: ## Test Coverage Gap Summary\n329: \n330: | Spec Requirement | Existing Test File | Gap Status |\n331: |---|---|---|\n332: | Data plane init failure recovery | `test_code_interpreter_client.py` | **Missing** |\n333: | Execute command timeout buffer (+2.0s) | `test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | **Missing** |\n334: | SA token file fallback | `test_control_plane.py` | **Missing** |\n335: | run_code write-file-then-execute flow | `test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | **Partial** — mocks delegation only |\n336: | Context manager exception propagation | `test_code_interpreter_client.py` | **Missing** |\n337: | Invoke per-request header isolation | `test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | **Partial** |\n338: | Multipart upload Content-Type absence | `test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | **Missing** |\n339: | Download path leading slash stripping | `test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | **Missing** |\n340: | Delete session 404 idempotency | `test_control_plane.py` | **Covered** |\n341: | Invoke response parsing | `test_agent_runtime_client.py` | **Covered** |\n342: | Package __all__ exports | No test file | **Missing** |\n343: | Create session URL/body contract | `test_control_plane.py` | **Partial** |\n344: | write_file base64 encoding | `test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | **Covered** |\n345: | Bootstrap session ID missing header | `test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | **Covered** |\n346: \n347: ---\n348: \n349: ## File Structure\n350: \n351: | Path | Role |\n352: |------|------|\n353: | `tests/test_code_interpreter_client.py` | **EXISTING** — extend with init failure, context manager exception tests |\n354: | `tests/test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | **EXISTING** — extend with timeout buffer, multipart headers, download path tests |\n355: | `tests/test_control_plane.py` | **EXISTING** — extend with SA token fallback tests |\n356: | `tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py` | **EXISTING** — extend with invoke response parsing edge cases |\n357: | `tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | **EXISTING** — extend with header isolation tests |\n358: | `tests/test_package_exports.py` | **NEW** — test `__all__` contents for `agentcube` and `agentcube.clients` |\n359: \n360: ## Dependencies\n361: \n362: - `pytest` — test framework (existing)\n363: - `unittest.mock` — mocking (existing, stdlib)\n364: - `requests` — HTTP client (existing dependency)\n\n(End of file - total 364 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-040: Python SDK/CLI 测试 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `sdk-python/tests`\n- **Language:** Python\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n\n## Scope\n\nThis delta spec defines the test coverage requirements for the AgentCube Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`). Existing tests cover basic initialization, delegation, and happy paths for all client classes. This spec identifies **gaps** between the existing test suite and the specification, and defines acceptance scenarios for the missing coverage.\n\n---\n\n## R-1: CodeInterpreterClient — data plane init failure recovery\n\n**Scope:** `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` — `__init__`, `_init_data_plane`\n\n### Requirement: Data plane init failure cleans up session","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-040/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775894741000,"end":1775894741006}}}}
